text:
Hi, my team is trying to use the batch upsert API but keep getting 404.  Here is a sample call :
```curl --location '<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v3/objects/contacts/batch/upsert>' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--header 'Accept: application/json' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer XXXXXX' \
--data-raw '{
  "inputs": [
    {
        "id":"55120122312",
      "properties": {
        "email":"testing@asdadsa.com",
                "firstname": "Test",
                "lastname": "Contact 123"
            }
    }
  ]
}'```
This returns :
```{
    "status": "error",
    "message": "resource not found",
    "correlationId": "7a0c10a7-035f-XXXXX-23e4e9eb7bff"
}```
From what I understand, upsert should be creating the record if it doesn't exist. Do we need to pass a specific `idProperty` value for it to work?

No luck with a custom unique id as well. :sad-panda:
```{
  "inputs": [
    {
        "idProperty":"test_id",
        "id":"55120122312",
      "properties": {
        "email":"<mailto:testing@test.com|testing@test.com>",
                "firstname": "Testing",
                "lastname": "Contact"
            }
    }
  ]
}```

Great. I didn't know we had upsert capabilities in the V3 CRM Objects API.

I haven't tried this myself. But can you try modifying your request body to include the `idProperty` like you suspected, as follows
```"inputs": [
    {
      "id":"<mailto:testing@asdadsa.com|testing@asdadsa.com>",
      "idProperty": "email",
      "properties": {
                "firstname": "Test",
                "lastname": "Contact 123"
            }
    }
  ]```
I think we need to use a property (other than the HubSpot Defined "Record Id" / "HubSpot Object Id") that is configured as unique as the idProperty

I think this is because the Record Id is set automatically by HubSpot and therefore we cannot set it ourself with an upsert.
